\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 23.     Traunsteinera}      Reichenb.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By R. de Soó. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Tubers 2, ovoid, entire. Perianth-segments ovate to ovate-lanceolate, acuminate or sometimes with spathulate apex. Labellum patent, 3-lobed, glabrous. Spur short. Rostellum 3-lobed, the middle lobe erect, linear-cucullate. Viscidia in a somewhat rudimentary, 2-lobed bursicle.
\par

