\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. T. globosa} (L.) Reichenb.,{\i  Fl. Saxon.} 87 (1842). Stem 15-65 cm, erect, curved, with 2-3 leaves and 2-3 pinkish bracts above. Leaves oblong-lanceolate or subobovate. Spike pyramidal-globose, becoming ellipsoid. Bracts lanceolate, 1- to 3-veined, as long as or longer than the ovary. Flowers pinkish-lilac; inner perianth-segments and labellum with purple spots. Outer perianth-segments 5-6 mm; inner slightly shorter. Labellum c. 4·5 × 3 mm, almost square, widened at the base, deeply 3-lobed to c. ½-way; lateral lobes ovate, obtuse or acute; middle lobe broadly oblong, the apex sometimes denticulate. Spur 1/3-1/2 as long as ovary, cylindric-conical, directed downwards. 2n = 42.{\i  Meadows, mainly in the mountains. From the Vosges and S. Poland southwards to N. Spain, N.C. Italy and S. Bulgaria.} ?Al Au Bu Cz Ga Ge He Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs (W, K).
