\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 24.      Orchis}       L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By R. de Soó. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Tubers 2-3, globose to ellipsoid, entire. Perianth-segments free, equal, or sometimes the inner smaller, all convergent into a galea or the outer patent and deflexed. Labellum porrect or slightly decurved, entire to 3-lobed, glabrous or papillose. Spur present. Bracts membranous. Rostellum 3-lobed, the middle lobe short, lamelliform. Viscidia in a 2-lobed bursicle.
